&quot;You may take your seats.&quot; he intoned in a bass rumble. We sat. &quot;We are here to try the case of the City of Silverdane vs. Lennon Mordril. The charges are two counts of first degree murder, with lesser charges of obstructing justice, tampering with a witness, unlawful entry, and interferring with the mating rituals of another race.&quot; The crowd stirred at that last part. They always loved a good sex scandal. Allimore smashed down his gavel and the mob quieted. He continued. &quot;For the sake of expediency, the jury will decide upon the major charges first; that is, the two murder charge, and then the lesser. I do not need to remind the jury that you are not to discuss the case with each other or with anyone else when you leave this courtroom. If anyone approaches you about the case...&quot; and he looked pointedly at Chelton Keller, who tried to shrink into himself, &quot;...you will report it to me or a court officer immediately and we will handle it. You will listen to the arguments of both the defense and the prosecution, and will decide if the defendant is innocent or guilty. In the case of a criminal trial, you must find him guilty BEYOND A REASONABLE DOUBT if you are to return a guilty verdict. You will be given as long as you need after closing arguments to decide on the defendant's guilt or innocence. Do you understand?&quot;<br>
